<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-74-0081 </DOCNO><TEXT>The article deals with secs. 43-46 of the Act on Administrative Procedure,especially regarding the adjusting of procedural defects. The consequencesof the 'Muelheim-Kaerlich decision' of the Federal Constitutional Courtare described. The author has the opinion that the annulment of an administrativeact is obligatory in case of infringement of constitutionally obligatoryprocedure, even if the decision was without alternative. (CW)</TEXT></DOC>